# GCON

> Decentralized Verified GPU Compute Network


Run GPU workloads on distributed providers with **cryptographic proof of execution**—without relying on blockchain consensus.

![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green.svg)
![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.12+-3776AB?logo=python&logoColor=white)
![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/Version-v0.10-orange)
![Execution](https://img.shields.io/badge/Execution-Verifiable-brightgreen)
![Network](https://img.shields.io/badge/Network-Decentralized-blueviolet)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-MVP-success)

---

## Why GCON?

Traditional GPU marketplaces let users rent compute, but they cannot prove that a workload was executed correctly.

GCON introduces **verifiable execution** through cryptographic receipts, execution evidence, and decentralized coordination, allowing customers to trust computation without trusting the provider.

---

## Key Features

-  Distributed GPU execution
-  Cryptographic proof of execution
-  Signed execution receipts
-  Job scheduling and orchestration
-  Distributed agent networking
-  Resource monitoring
-  Artifact registry
-  Open-source architecture

---

## Architecture

```text
        Customer
            │
            ▼
     Job Coordinator
            │
     ┌──────┴──────┐
     ▼             ▼
  Agent A       Agent B
     │             │
     ▼             ▼
 GPU Worker    GPU Worker
     │             │
     └──────┬──────┘
            ▼
     Receipt Generator
            │
            ▼
       Verification
```

